---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import Button from "../global/Button.astro";
---

<style lang="scss">
  @use "../../styles/all" as *;

  .aboutSection {
    width: 100vw;
    display: flex;
    // align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-direction: row;

    .aboutContainer {
      color: $white;
      width: 50vw;
      margin-top: 2%;

      h1 {
        font-size: 5ch;
        letter-spacing: 0.02em;

        &::after {
          content: "";
          width: 80%;
          display: block;
          background-color: $orange;
          height: 0.5vh;
        }
      }
      p {
        width: 80%;
        line-height: 1.6;
      }
    }

    .imageContainer {
      width: 40vw;

      img {
        width: 100%;
        height: auto;
        vertical-align: middle;
        font-style: italic;
        background-repeat: no-repeat;
        background-size: cover;
        shape-margin: 1rem;
        object-fit: cover;
        aspect-ratio: 1 / 1;
        display: block;

        object-position: center;
        background-attachment: fixed;
        background-position: center;
      }
    }
  }
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .aboutSection {
      width: 100vw;
      flex-direction: column-reverse;
      justify-content: center;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 1.5vh;
      margin-top: 4%;

      .aboutContainer {
        width: 80vw;

        h1 {
          // text-align: center;

          &::after {
            // width: 100%;
          }
        }

        p {
          text-align: left;
          align-self: center;
          width: 70vw;
        }
      }

      .imageContainer {
        width: 100vw;

        img {
          margin: 0 auto;
          width: 80%;
        }
      }
    }
  }
</style>

<section class="aboutSection">
  <section class="aboutContainer">
    <h1>Climbing Coach and Enthusiast</h1>
    <p>
      Hi! I&#39;m Jesse, a climber, developer, training geek, and climbing
      philosopher. One time, my friends started calling me J-Fire, for better or
      worse. I started climbing in 2007, in a humble converted racquetball court
      at my university. I remember those days well. I was instantly hooked on
      the joy and simplicity of the movement. It&#39;s not an understatement to
      say that climbing changed my life. And what makes climbing so incredible
      is the number of people I meet out at the crag who feel the same way.
      It&#39;s both obvious and yet baffling how something so elegantly simple
      can have such a profound impact on all kinds of different people.
    </p>
    <p>
      Not sure where your climbing is going? Overwhelmed by a thousand instagram
      posts suggesting a million different things you should go do right now to
      get better at climbing? It&#39;s not just you. We live in an age of
      overwhelming information. One of the best things I can do as a coach is
      help you cut through the noise and figure out what to do with your
      climbing.
    </p>
    <Button cta="Learn More" link="/coaching">
